		<section>
			<section.front>
				<doc.title toc-guid="I0d4b947bc08511d88885080020ab8e66">
					<head parent="doc.title">
						<label.name>&#167; </label.name>
						<label.designator>1:6.</label.designator>
						<headtext>Applicability of Federal Truth in Lending Act, Real Estate Settlement Procedures Act, and Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act</headtext>
					</head>
				</doc.title>
			</section.front>
			<section.body>
					<para>
						<paratext>The taxpayer is conducting a business and the ordinary and reasonable expenses of the business are deductible against income realized from the operation.</paratext>
					</para>
					<?page no="24"?>
					<para>
						<paratext>The second category<footnote.reference refid="I01a2f010680911e88f4a9c1f64100801">1</footnote.reference> of real estate is property used as a personal residence. This is technically a capital asset, which is the next category to be discussed.</paratext>
					</para>
					<?page no="25"?>
					<para>
						<paratext>Being a personal<footnote.reference refid="I01a2f010680911e88f4a9c1f64100802">9</footnote.reference> residence, however, causes different tax doctrines to apply. Gain on the sale of a residence held for longer than one year is taxed as long-term capital gain.</paratext>
					</para>
			</section.body>
		</section>
